            "title": "Weird Keys 🤪",
            "content": "What if your key has a space in it?\n\n`let obj = { 'full name': 'John Doe' };`\n\n`obj.full name` creates an Error!"
        },
        {
            "id": "s_l3_2",
            "type": "quiz",
            "title": "Quick Check 🧠",
            "content": "",
            "quizData": {
                "id": "q_l3_1",
                "type": "multiple_choice",
                "question": "Can variable names have spaces?",
                "options": [
                    {
                        "id": "opt1",
                        "text": "Yes",
                        "isCorrect": false
                    },
                    {
                        "id": "opt2",
                        "text": "No",
                        "isCorrect": true
                    }
                ],
                "explanation": "Spaces break variable names, so dot notation fails."
            }
        },
        {
            "id": "s_l3_3",
            "type": "code",
            "title": "Use Brackets []",
            "content": "If the key is a string with spaces or special characters, use `['key']`.",
            "codeSnippet": "let user = { 'full name': 'Anna' };\nconsole.log(user['full name']);",
            "codeLanguage": "javascript",
            "canRunCode": true
        },
        {
            "id": "s_l3_4",
            "type": "code",
            "title": "Dynamic Keys 🔄",
            "content": "You can also use a **variable** inside the brackets!\n\nThis is super powerful.",
            "codeSnippet": "let key = 'age';\nlet user = { age: 25 };\n\nconsole.log(user[key]); // 25\nconsole.log(user.key); // undefined (looks for key named \"key\")",
            "codeLanguage": "javascript",
            "canRunCode": true
        },
